article.description: — Po'Boigh King had 34 points, Fred Cleveland Jr. scored 25 with 10 assists and North Carolina Central beat Delaware State 93-81 on Monday night.
article.headline: King, Cleveland help North Carolina Central top Delaware State 93-81
article.linkText: King, Cleveland help North Carolina Central top Delaware State 93-81
article.story: DURHAM, N.C. -- — Po'Boigh King had 34 points, Fred Cleveland Jr. scored 25 with 10 assists and North Carolina Central beat Delaware State 93-81 on Monday night. King grabbed eight rebounds for the Eagles (15-11, 7-4 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Cleveland made 4 of 9 shots from 3-point range. Keishon Porter scored 12. The Hornets (12-15, 5-6) were led by Martez Robinson's 27 points and eight rebounds. Deywilk Tavarez totaled 21 points and four assists. Cameron Stitt scored 13. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
